         <abstract>
            <p>This paper is the last in a series of three which analyze an adaptive approximate approach for solving $(n + 1)$-dimensional boundary value problems by replacing them with systems of equations in $n$-dimensional space. In this paper we show how to find reliable a posteriori estimates for the error and how these can also be used in the design of an adaptive strategy. Various numerical examples are contained in the paper.</p>
          </abstract>
